source:
The progress bar component, prefixed by <span class="gds-text--code">gds-progress-bar</span>, is a single element component. It accepts a data-value attribute with an integer value between 0 and 100, which is used to style the component and indicate elapsed progress of an event.

@section {String} section Atoms

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent Progress Bar

@name {String} name Progress Bar

@example {Code}

<div class="gds-progress-bar -m-b-2" data-value="35"></div>
<div class="gds-progress-bar -m-b-2 gds-progress-bar--sm" data-value="42"></div>
<div class="gds-progress-bar -m-b-2 gds-progress-bar--lg" data-value="53"></div>
<div class="gds-progress-bar gds-progress-bar--striped-primary gds-progress-bar--animated" data-value="55"></div>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup true

@author {String} author Myles O'Connor

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger gds-progress-bar
@defaultClasses {Array} defaultClasses gds-progress-bar
@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses gds-progress-bar--lg,gds-progress-bar--sm,gds-progress-bar--striped-primary,gds-progress-bar--secondary,gds-progress-bar--striped-secondary,gds-progress-bar--animated,gds-progress-bar--value-colors

The segment component is used to wrap content in an optionally collapsible container.  It's prefixed by <span class="gds-text--code">gds-segment</span> and the content you want contained by it is inserted inside. Use the attribute <span class="gds-text--code">data-gds-segment="x"</span> where X is a unique ID that corresponds with a <span class="gds-text--code">data-gds-divider</span> ID.

@section {String} section Atoms

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent Segment

@name {String} name Segment

@example {Code}

<div class="gds-segment" data-gds-segment="1">Content Goes Here</div>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup false

@author {String} author Dan McKenna

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger gds-segment

@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses gds-segment--collapse

