</div>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup true

@author {String} author Dan McKenna

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger gds-form-group__range-input

@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses

Dual range slider inputs allow users to click and drag two points until a desired range of values is reached.  You can initialize this component using <span class="gds-text--code">$(input-id or data attribute).gdsRangeSlider(optionsObject)</span>.  It accepts these options: <span class="gds-text--code">minVal:Number</span>,<span class="gds-text--code">maxValue:Number</span>,<span class="gds-text--code">initialVal:Array(Number,Number)</span>  You can return the values of the slider like so: <span class="gds-text--code">$(slider).gdsRangeSlider().get()</span>. and manually set those values at any time by doing <span class="gds-text--code">$(slider).gdsRangeSlider().set(options)</span>.  The options object passed to set is identical in structure to the one used for initialization.


@section {String} section Molecules

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent Input

@name {String} name Input - Dual Range Slider

@example {Code}

<div class="gds-form-group -m-b-1">
---]<label class="gds-form-group__label" for="range-input-1" >Dual Selector Range Input (Requires JS)</label>
---]<div class="gds-form-group__range-input gds-form-group__range-input--dual" id="range-input-1" data-gds-dual-range-slider>
---]---]<div class="gds-form-group__range-wrapper" data-gds-range-wrapper>
---]---]---]<div class="gds-form-group__range-thumb gds-form-group__range-thumb--dual" data-gds-range-thumb></div>
---]---]---]<div class="gds-form-group__range-thumb gds-form-group__range-thumb--dual" data-gds-range-thumb></div>
---]---]</div>
---]---]<div class="gds-form-group__range-track" data-gds-range-track>
---]---]---]<div class="gds-form-group__range-selected" data-gds-range-selected></div>
---]---]</div>
---]</div>
</div>

